attributes.title: We Ship My Little Pony, Fans, and Cosplayers with John de Lancie
attributes.caption: Nobody expected My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic to make the impact that it did. 10 years after its debut, we ship this phenomenon with our own Ponypalooza hosted by Twilight Sparkle herself, Tara Strong, with John de Lancie, cosplayers, and fans.
attributes.description: Nobody expected My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic to make the impact that it did, and certainly not with such a wide spectrum of fans. 10 years after its debut, we ship this phenomenon with our own Ponypalooza, hosted by Twilight Sparkle herself, Tara Strong. We begin our journey with John de Lancie, the iconic actor who voiced Discord. We’ll then chat with a fan whose life was drastically influenced by MLP and its community, and, finally, meet some magical cosplayers who spread pony-style friendship in real-life. And don’t miss part two, featuring a colossal cast reunion, a surprise celebrity superfan, and champions of the Brony community.
attributes.display_title: We Ship My Little Pony, Fans, and Cosplayers with John de Lancie

attributes.title: We Ship My Little Pony with a Cast Reunion plus Bella & Billy Bob Thornton
attributes.caption: My Little Pony’s cast proves that Friendship really is Magic. Join us for an ‘Inside the Pony Actor’s Studio’ Q&A led by super fans Bella & Billy Bob Thornton. It’s an acting master class that reveals the secret origins of these iconic pony personas.
attributes.description: My Little Pony’s cast proves that Friendship really is Magic. Join us for an ‘Inside the Pony Actor’s Studio’ Q&A led by super fans Bella & Billy Bob Thornton. It’s a master class in acting that reveals the secret origins and inspirations behind some of these iconic pony personas.
attributes.display_title: We Ship My Little Pony with a Cast Reunion plus Bella & Billy Bob Thornton

attributes.title: My Little Pony: Fandom is Magic Featuring Brony Community All-Stars - Part 3 of 3
attributes.caption: My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic is a special show, but that's largely due to fandom surrounding it. From crafting to conventions to causes, the Brony community is unparalleled. Today, we speak with folks who started as fans, but became much more.
attributes.description:
My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic is a special show, but much of that is because of the fandom that surrounds it. From crafting to conventions to causes, the Brony community is unparalleled in all of pop culture. In the conclusion to our 3-part Ponypalooza, we speak with some “horse famous” organizers and artists who may have started as fans, but became much more.
Special thanks to Scribbaroo for the incredible “Dorby” animation. Do we smell a spin-off?
attributes.display_title: My Little Pony: Fandom is Magic Featuring Brony Community All-Stars - Part 3 of 3

attributes.title: We Ship Ichigo, Orihime, and Rukia with the Cast of Bleach
attributes.caption: We ship anime and dimensions beyond with the cast of Bleach — Johnny Yong Bosch, Michelle Ruff, and Stephanie Sheh! While Ichigo, Rukia, and Orihime handle the hollows on TV, we explore the real-life ramifications of extra-dimensional energies.
attributes.description:
We ship anime and dimensions beyond with the cast of Bleach — Johnny Yong Bosch, Michelle Ruff, and Stephanie Sheh! While Ichigo, Rukia, and Orihime handle the hollows on TV, we explore the real-life ramifications of extra-dimensional energies with Tara’s spiritual guru Evan McCormick.
Spoiler alert if you don’t want to know how the manga ends!
attributes.display_title: We Ship Ichigo, Orihime, and Rukia with the Cast of Bleach

attributes.title: We Ship Bleach Cosplayers with International Cosplay Artists
attributes.caption: Bleach is an inspiration to fans around the world, and these cosplayers reflect the beauty and talent of both its fandom and message. Let's explore what makes this anime series special, and what brought these incredible artists into the world of cosplay.
attributes.description:
Bleach has been an inspiration to fans around the world, and these cosplayers reflect the beauty and talent of both its fandom and its message.
Tara and Greg explore what makes this anime series special, and what brought these incredible artists into the world of cosplay.
If you missed our episode with the English-language cast of Bleach, be sure to give it a watch, listen, or both!
attributes.display_title: We Ship Bleach Cosplayers with International Cosplay Artists

attributes.title: We Ship Cyborg & Jinx with Khary Payton and Lauren Tom
attributes.caption: After 20 years of Teen Titans, CyJinx is a ship that hits close to home for Tara & Greg — plus it’s an excuse to reunite with fellow Titan Khary Payton and frenemy Lauren Tom, the voices of Cyborg and Jinx, for fanfic and behind the scenes stories.
attributes.description:
After 20 years of Teen Titans, CyJinx is a ship that hits close to home for Tara & Greg — plus it’s an excuse to reunite with fellow Titan Khary Payton and on-screen frenemy Lauren Tom, the voices of Cyborg and Jinx. We’ll walk down memory lane, read fanfic, and celebrate our love for these characters and each other.
We’re also honored to welcome some extra special guests, including an artist who credits her Teen Titans fan art with sparking her career, and the Montalto family, who are keeping their daughter’s memory alive through an incredible foundation that’s making a positive impact on the world.
attributes.display_title: We Ship Cyborg & Jinx with Khary Payton and Lauren Tom

attributes.title: We Ship Cyborg & Jinx Cosplay and Teen Titans Fandom
attributes.caption: Booyah! Let’s celebrate Teen Titans fandom with some fabulous cosplayers. Cyborg isn’t an easy costume and Jinx isn’t the most obvious character, so we need to explore what makes these characters so inspiring. Also — what’s the perfect CyJinx date?
attributes.description: Booyah! Let’s celebrate Teen Titans fandom with some fabulous cosplayers. Cyborg isn’t an easy costume and Jinx isn’t the most obvious character, so we need to explore what makes these characters so inspiring. Also — what’s the perfect CyJinx date?
attributes.display_title: We Ship Cyborg & Jinx Cosplay and Teen Titans Fandom

attributes.title: We Ship Joker & Harley Quinn with Troy Baker, Chad Hardin, and Amanda Wyatt
attributes.caption: The Joker and Harley Quinn have a crazy love. What makes them so special, and how do you step into such iconic clown shoes? Troy Baker brings the voice, Amanda Wyatt brings the direction, and Chad Hardin brings the art to put a smile on your face.
attributes.description: The Joker and Harley Quinn have a crazy love, and we have crazy love for these characters. What makes them so special, and how can anyone step into such iconic clown shoes? Troy Baker brings the voice, Amanda Wyatt brings the direction, and Chad Hardin brings the art in an episode that’s sure to put a smile on your face … whether you like it or not! But seriously — give us a like, and stick around for some surprises.
attributes.display_title: We Ship Joker & Harley Quinn with Troy Baker, Chad Hardin, and Amanda Wyatt

attributes.title: We Ship Harley Quinn & Joker Cosplay
attributes.caption: The king and queen of cosplay have to be the Joker and Harley Quinn. If you’ve been to any convention ever, it’s obvious. What makes these characters so irresistible? We invited some of our favorite cosplayers to explore the magic behind the madness.
attributes.description: The king and queen of cosplay have to be the Joker and Harley Quinn. If you’ve been to any convention ever, it’s obvious. What makes these characters so irresistible? We invited some of our favorite Joker & Harley cosplayers to explore the magic behind the madness.
attributes.display_title: We Ship Harley Quinn & Joker Cosplay

attributes.title: We Ship RWBY with the Creative Team of Rooster Teeth’s Hit American Anime Series
attributes.caption: An American anime produced in Texas? That seemed crazy — until RWBY proved that crazy dreams come true. The show’s creative team reveal the unorthodox path that both RWBY and their careers have taken to get here.
attributes.description: An American anime produced in Texas? That seemed crazy — until RWBY proved that crazy dreams come true. The show’s creative team reveal the unorthodox path that both RWBY and their careers have taken to get here. Video games, fanfic, and a passion for anime collide in Rooster Teeth’s global, hit series.
attributes.display_title: We Ship RWBY with the Creative Team of Rooster Teeth’s Hit American Anime Series

attributes.title: We Ship RWBY with the Show’s Stars and Cosplayers - Part Two of Two
attributes.caption: The passion for RWBY is undeniable. What is it about this American anime show that inspires its fans so deeply? How do marketing and editor jobs lead to starring voice acting roles in a global, hit series? How can cosplayers choose just one character?
attributes.description: The passion for RWBY is undeniable. What is it about this singular American anime show that inspires its fans so deeply? How do marketing and editor jobs lead to starring voice acting roles in a global, hit series? How can cosplayers choose just one character to play? Are cookie parties the secret to building a community of hungry fans? All this and more as we bring our RWBY ship home!
attributes.display_title: We Ship RWBY with the Show’s Stars and Cosplayers - Part Two of Two

attributes.title: Danny Phantom Reunion with Its Cast and Creator
attributes.caption: There’s competition for Danny Phantom’s love — Sam, Paulina, Valerie, Lil Nas X. No one would ghost this supernatural superhero. Creator Butch Hartman and voices of Danny, Sam, and Jazz explore the show's origins and the call to return it from the dead.
attributes.description:
Want Danny Phantom’s love? There’s a lot of competition — Sam, Paulina, Valerie, Lil Nas X, etc. What we can all agree on is that none of us would ghost this supernatural superhero.
Speaking with the show’s creator Butch Hartman, and its cast, David Kaufman (Danny), Grey DeLisle-Griffin (Sam), and Colleen O'Shaughnessey (Jazz), we explore the inspirations for this spooky series, how the actors were cast, and the passion that fans have to see it return from the dead.
attributes.display_title: Danny Phantom Reunion with Its Cast and Creator

attributes.title: The Ship-it Show takes on Death Battle!
attributes.caption: Our friends from Death Battle pay us a visit to flip-the-script for something we call Battle Ships! Instead of fighting to the death, can’t we just hug it out?
attributes.description: Our friends from Death Battle pay us a visit to flip-the-script for something we call Battle Ships! Instead of fighting to the death, can’t we just hug it out? Special thanks to everyone who tuned into the live edition of this episode. This is an edited version, but feel free to keep donating to the George Floyd Memorial Foundation!
attributes.display_title: The Ship-it Show takes on Death Battle!

attributes.title: We Ship Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles with Kevin Eastman & Ciro Nieli
attributes.caption: The Ninja Turtles have rebooted many times since their first, self-published comic books — but Nickelodeon’s 2012 series kicks the most shell. TMNT co-creator Kevin Eastman, 2012 show runner Ciro Nieli, and Michelangelo voice Greg Cipes talk turtle!
attributes.description: The Ninja Turtles have been rebooted many times since Kevin Eastman sketched his first Michelangelo and self-published a few thousand comic books — but Nickelodeon’s 2012 reboot may kick the most shell. The architect of that reboot, Ciro Nieli, joins TMNT co-creator Kevin Eastman, and Michelangelo himself, Greg Cipes, to talk Turtle Power. Cowabooyakasha!
attributes.display_title: We Ship Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles with Kevin Eastman & Ciro Nieli

attributes.title: The Legendary Rob Paulsen joins Special Guests for a Live Shiptacular
attributes.caption: Remember when Tara auditioned future husbands? Greg’s bottomless burrito? This live episode was wild. Rob Paulsen (Yakko, Pinky, Raphael, Donatello) is joined by Bullwinkle voice Brad Norman, author Ben Jackson, and Detroit Lions pro Tyrell Crosby.
attributes.description: Remember when Tara auditioned future ex-husbands? Greg’s bottomless burrito? This live episode was wild. The legendary Rob Paulsen joins us and reveals that he’s not just a man of many characters (Yakko, Pinky, Raphael AND Donatello?!), he’s a man of many insights. Brad Norman joins Tara for a Rocky & Bullwinkle reunion, Ben Jackson reveals secrets of convention green rooms, and Tyrell Crosby of the Detroit Lions parties with this gathering of Michiganders.
attributes.display_title: The Legendary Rob Paulsen joins Special Guests for a Live Shiptacular

attributes.title: We Ship DC Super Hero Girls Bumblebee with Kimberly Brooks and Gene Vassilaros
attributes.caption: It’s a mini DC Super Hero Girls reunion (pun intended) as Kimberly Brooks, aka Bumblebee, joins Tara, aka Batgirl and Harley Quinn, voice director Gene Vassilaros, and, of course Greg “Beast Boy” Cipes.
attributes.description:
It’s a mini DC Super Hero Girls reunion (pun intended) as Kimberly Brooks, aka Bumblebee, joins Tara, aka Batgirl and Harley Quinn, voice director Gene Vassilaros, and, of course Greg “Beast Boy” Cipes.
This one is big on origin stories — tackling how grade school teachers, commercials, and live action film can lead to careers in animation. Get ready for inspiration and advice on how to take what you want from the universe!
attributes.display_title: We Ship DC Super Hero Girls Bumblebee with Kimberly Brooks and Gene Vassilaros

attributes.title: Cosplay Shiptacular with Yaya Han and MCroft07
attributes.caption: Cosplay is an art that takes many forms. We’re talking to two incredible artists who make cosplay magic in different ways. Yaya Han literally wrote the book on cosplay, while Melissa Croft prefers to point her pens at herself as a body painter.
attributes.description: You know we ship cosplay, but it’s an art that takes many forms. We’re talking to two incredible artists who make cosplay magic in different ways. Yaya Han literally wrote the book on cosplay, while Melissa Croft prefers to point her pens at herself as a body painter. Edited from a Live Show (May 11, 2021)

attributes.title: Bumblebee Cosplay and Tara & Greg Find Their Characters
attributes.caption: You know a Bumblebee inspired episode has to be buzz worthy, so we brought a swarm of cosplayers on to flip-the-ship and explore both their journeys and Tara & Greg’s process for finding characters.
attributes.description: You know a Bumblebee inspired episode has to be buzz worthy, so we brought a swarm of cosplayers on to flip-the-ship and explore both their journeys and Tara & Greg’s process for finding characters. We reveal how Tara found Raven’s voice, Greg’s creative contributions to the Fast & Furious franchise, and how the Teen Titans family saved Tara’s butt (literally) when her Batgirl costume split at a convention.
attributes.display_title: Bumblebee Cosplay and Tara & Greg Find Their Characters

attributes.title: We Ship Naruto with an English Voice Cast Reunion
attributes.caption: Believe it! Naruto's English language cast share behind-the-scenes hijinks from the mega-hit anime series. Maile Flanagan (Naruto), Yuri Lowenthal (Sasuke), Steve Blum (Orochimaru), and director Mary Elizabeth McGlynn have wild stories to tell.
attributes.description: Believe it! The English language cast of Naruto reunites to share some behind-the-scenes hijinks from the mega-hit anime series. Maile Flanagan (Naruto), Yuri Lowenthal (Sasuke), Steve Blum (Orochimaru), and director Mary Elizabeth McGlynn reveal their most outrageous convention memories, their most memorable fan encounters, and how they got their roles — including one that started with a promise of free pizza.
attributes.display_title: We Ship Naruto with an English Voice Cast Reunion
